Companion (bottom-screen barter) — per-instance item identity (Bug 2).

Layered on companion-barter-export.patch. That patch exported both "id" and "sid"
as the plain record id, so two same-record stacks (e.g. one worn Bonemold Boot +
one unworn) were indistinguishable, and companionFindIndex resolved a borrow/return
by record id — returning the FIRST match in the model's sort order, which (ItemStack
type ascending: Barter < Equipped < Normal) is the EQUIPPED stack. Selling the
unequipped copy therefore sold the equipped one.

Fix: give every physical stack object a session-stable per-instance handle
"<refId>#<ordinal>", stored in gCompanionSid keyed on the stable LiveCellRefBase*
(GM_Barter pauses the sim; staging only re-categorizes an item's ItemStack type
without changing its object, so the handle survives every borrow/return with NO
re-export). It is emitted as the "sid" field (BarterItem.stackId on the Kotlin
side, which the DS now sends in CMP:barter_borrow/return), and companionFindIndex
matches on it instead of the record id. A split stack's remainder + staged half
share one object → one sid; the existing borrowed (Type_Barter) filter disambiguates
them. Populated once per session in companionExportOpen; the map is cleared there so
ordinals restart per merchant.
